# Mineflayer Bots

Reference: [Mineflayer](https://mineflayer.com/) · [GitHub PrismarineJS/mineflayer](https://github.com/PrismarineJS/mineflayer)

## Config and secrets

- **No hardcoded secrets.** Use `.env` and `dotenv`: `require('dotenv').config()` at top; read `MC_HOST`, `MC_PORT`, `MC_USERNAME`, `MC_VERSION`, `MC_AUTH`, and any login/passwords from `process.env`.
- Provide `.env.example` with variable names and empty or placeholder values; keep `.env` in `.gitignore`.
- Require `MC_HOST` and `MC_USERNAME` (or equivalent) when missing: `console.error` and `process.exit(1)`.

## Creating the bot

```js
const bot = mineflayer.createBot({
  host: process.env.MC_HOST,
  port: parseInt(process.env.MC_PORT || '25565', 10),
  username: process.env.MC_USERNAME,
  version: process.env.MC_VERSION || '1.21.11',
  auth: process.env.MC_AUTH || 'offline',
  hideErrors: true  // optional: suppress protocol parse errors from server
});
```

## Essential events

- `bot.on('login', () => ...)` — after connection.
- `bot.on('spawn', () => ...)` — in world; send server login command here if needed (from env).
- `bot.on('chat', (username, message) => ...)` — ignore own: `if (username === bot.username) return`.
- `bot.on('kicked', (reason) => ...)` and `bot.on('error', (err) => ...)` — log and handle.
- `bot.on('end', (reason) => ...)` — schedule reconnect with `setTimeout(createBot, delay)` if desired.

## World and blocks

- **Find block:** `bot.findBlock({ matching: (b) => b.name === 'diamond_ore', maxDistance: 32 })` → single block or `null`.
- **Find blocks:** `bot.findBlocks({ matching: id => id === 56, maxDistance: 16, count: 5 })` → array of positions (closest first).
- **Block at position:** `bot.blockAt(vec3)`.
- **Entity:** `bot.nearestEntity(entity => entity.name === 'cow')`.

## Chat and movement

- `bot.chat(message)` — public chat (Minecraft chat length limit ~256 chars; split if needed).
- Movement: `bot.setControlState('forward', true)` / `false`; keys: `forward`, `back`, `left`, `right`, `jump`, `sprint`, `sneak`.
- Position: `bot.entity.position` (Vec3).

## Version support

Mineflayer supports 1.8–1.21.11. Set `version` in createBot when the server uses a specific version (e.g. `1.21.11`).

## Autonomous package (`mc-bot/autonomous`)

- Load `.env` from the package root early (`dotenv` with `path.join(__dirname, '.env')` in `bot.js`) so `STATE_FILE` and other vars are visible before any `require` that reads `process.env` at load time.
- **Username/host:** `NAME` / `SERVER_IP` / `PORT` / `VERSION` override `MC_HOST` / `MC_USERNAME` / `MC_PORT` / `MC_VERSION` (see `lib/config.js`). `VERSION=latest` is normalized to `1.21.11`.
- **Server login plugins:** If chat is locked until login, set `MC_LOGIN_CMD` (e.g. `/login …`) and send it on **first spawn**, then send public spawn chat after `MC_LOGIN_CHAT_DELAY_MS` (same pattern as `viewer/bot.js`). Without this, the bot may connect but never “appear” in public chat.
- **Online auth:** Set `MC_PASSWORD` (or `MC_PASS`) when using non-offline auth; pass it as `password` in `createBot`.
- **Spawn chat:** Log every outgoing public message with a stable prefix (e.g. `[Bot] Chat:`) so operators and tests can confirm the bot is talking. Keep greeting configurable via `MC_SPAWN_CHAT`; autonomous default can differ from basic.
- **Human-like movement:** Prefer `allow1by1towers=false` for pathfinder in autonomous unless explicitly needed; it avoids bot-like scaffold towers when chopping trees.
- **Early survival realism:** Prioritize food like a real player: if hunger is low and inventory has no edible items, hunt nearby passive mobs (`cow/pig/chicken/sheep/rabbit`) and eat before resuming gather/craft roadmap.
- **Mineflayer `spawn`:** May fire more than once (e.g. dimension changes). Run server login + public hello only once per connection; still refresh pathfinder movements on every spawn.
- **Live smoke test:** `npm run test:yolo` (or `node tests/run-all.js --yolo`) runs `tests/integration-yolo.test.js` against a real server; requires `NAME`/`MC_USERNAME` and host in `.env`. Default `npm test` stays offline/unit-only.
